<div class="quotetitle">mattheweston wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />So any assembler that can "assemble" 6502 code will work?<br /></div><br />Yes. You just have to make sure that they output a file that respects the structure of a NES ROM. NES ROMs contain a 16-byte header, followed by the PRG-ROM banks and then the CHR-ROM banks (if the game uses CHR-RAM there are no CHR-ROM banks in the ROM).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Fri Feb 12, 2010 5:47 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
